<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="376" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,572,1009,1072]" box="[151,217,1046,1072]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">
<figureCitation box="[151,217,1046,1072]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,248,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[263,1326,187,1892]" captionTargetId="figure-26@2.[259,1329,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. I. furcaprocessus sp. nov. A, F, K, holotype. A–E, adult, dorsal view; F–J, adult, lateral view; K–O, face; P, male pygofer and subgential plate, lateral view; Q, valve; R, connective, style and aedeagus, dorsal view; S, aedeagus, lateral view." pageId="1" pageNumber="376">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1117,1936]" box="[151,1380,1117,1145]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1117,1143]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">Description.</emphasis>
Small-sized species. Body length (including forewing): male, 
<quantity box="[998,1136,1118,1145]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.35" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="4.2" pageId="1" pageNumber="376" unit="mm" value="4.35" valueMax="4.5" valueMin="4.2">4.2–4.5 mm</quantity>
; female, 
<quantity box="[1238,1376,1118,1144]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="4.8" metricValueMin="4.2" pageId="1" pageNumber="376" unit="mm" value="4.5" valueMax="4.8" valueMin="4.2">4.2–4.8 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1117,1936]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1153,1179]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">Coloration.</emphasis>
General color light brown. Crown (
<figureCitation box="[744,866,1154,1180]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,248,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[263,1326,187,1892]" captionTargetId="figure-26@2.[259,1329,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. I. furcaprocessus sp. nov. A, F, K, holotype. A–E, adult, dorsal view; F–J, adult, lateral view; K–O, face; P, male pygofer and subgential plate, lateral view; Q, valve; R, connective, style and aedeagus, dorsal view; S, aedeagus, lateral view." pageId="1" pageNumber="376">Fig. 1A–O</figureCitation>
) and pronotum with darker brown markings, eyes (
<figureCitation box="[160,282,1190,1216]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,248,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[263,1326,187,1892]" captionTargetId="figure-26@2.[259,1329,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. I. furcaprocessus sp. nov. A, F, K, holotype. A–E, adult, dorsal view; F–J, adult, lateral view; K–O, face; P, male pygofer and subgential plate, lateral view; Q, valve; R, connective, style and aedeagus, dorsal view; S, aedeagus, lateral view." pageId="1" pageNumber="376">Fig. 1A–O</figureCitation>
) yellowish in 
<typeStatus box="[444,542,1190,1216]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">holotype</typeStatus>
(brown to darker brown in 
<typeStatus box="[857,970,1190,1216]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">paratypes</typeStatus>
). Clypeus (
<figureCitation box="[1101,1223,1190,1216]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,248,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[263,1326,187,1892]" captionTargetId="figure-26@2.[259,1329,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. I. furcaprocessus sp. nov. A, F, K, holotype. A–E, adult, dorsal view; F–J, adult, lateral view; K–O, face; P, male pygofer and subgential plate, lateral view; Q, valve; R, connective, style and aedeagus, dorsal view; S, aedeagus, lateral view." pageId="1" pageNumber="376">Fig. 1K–O</figureCitation>
) black. Pronotum, scutellum and face brown to darker brown. Forewings (
<figureCitation box="[771,890,1226,1252]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,248,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[263,1326,187,1892]" captionTargetId="figure-26@2.[259,1329,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. I. furcaprocessus sp. nov. A, F, K, holotype. A–E, adult, dorsal view; F–J, adult, lateral view; K–O, face; P, male pygofer and subgential plate, lateral view; Q, valve; R, connective, style and aedeagus, dorsal view; S, aedeagus, lateral view." pageId="1" pageNumber="376">Fig. 1A–E</figureCitation>
) clavus with large yellow transcommissural spot bordered with dark brown. Legs (
<figureCitation box="[529,639,1262,1288]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,248,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[263,1326,187,1892]" captionTargetId="figure-26@2.[259,1329,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. I. furcaprocessus sp. nov. A, F, K, holotype. A–E, adult, dorsal view; F–J, adult, lateral view; K–O, face; P, male pygofer and subgential plate, lateral view; Q, valve; R, connective, style and aedeagus, dorsal view; S, aedeagus, lateral view." pageId="1" pageNumber="376">Fig. 1F–J</figureCitation>
) yellow white to green.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1117,1936]" box="[199,940,1297,1324]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,374,1297,1323]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">Wing venation</emphasis>
. Forewing with only middle subapical cell closed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1117,1936]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,376,1333,1360]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[486,567,1334,1360]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,248,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[263,1326,187,1892]" captionTargetId="figure-26@2.[259,1329,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. I. furcaprocessus sp. nov. A, F, K, holotype. A–E, adult, dorsal view; F–J, adult, lateral view; K–O, face; P, male pygofer and subgential plate, lateral view; Q, valve; R, connective, style and aedeagus, dorsal view; S, aedeagus, lateral view." pageId="1" pageNumber="376">Fig. 1P</figureCitation>
) relatively long in lateral view. Male valve (
<figureCitation box="[1062,1146,1334,1360]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,248,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1398,215,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-26@4.[179,1408,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. I. longiprocessus sp. nov. A, adult, dorsal view; B, face; C, adult, lateral view; D, pygofer and subgential plate, lateral view; E, valve; F, connective, style and aedeagus, dorsal view; G, aedeagus, lateral view." pageId="1" pageNumber="376">Fig. 2E</figureCitation>
) basal margin not curved, apex convex medially, with a sharp projection. Subgenital plate (
<figureCitation box="[878,960,1370,1396]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,248,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[263,1326,187,1892]" captionTargetId="figure-26@2.[259,1329,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. I. furcaprocessus sp. nov. A, F, K, holotype. A–E, adult, dorsal view; F–J, adult, lateral view; K–O, face; P, male pygofer and subgential plate, lateral view; Q, valve; R, connective, style and aedeagus, dorsal view; S, aedeagus, lateral view." pageId="1" pageNumber="376">Fig. 1P</figureCitation>
) with dorsal margin broadly convex, apex rounded. Connective (
<figureCitation box="[399,481,1406,1432]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,248,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[263,1326,187,1892]" captionTargetId="figure-26@2.[259,1329,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. I. furcaprocessus sp. nov. A, F, K, holotype. A–E, adult, dorsal view; F–J, adult, lateral view; K–O, face; P, male pygofer and subgential plate, lateral view; Q, valve; R, connective, style and aedeagus, dorsal view; S, aedeagus, lateral view." pageId="1" pageNumber="376">Fig. 1P</figureCitation>
) with short stem. Style (
<figureCitation box="[756,842,1406,1432]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,248,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[263,1326,187,1892]" captionTargetId="figure-26@2.[259,1329,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. I. furcaprocessus sp. nov. A, F, K, holotype. A–E, adult, dorsal view; F–J, adult, lateral view; K–O, face; P, male pygofer and subgential plate, lateral view; Q, valve; R, connective, style and aedeagus, dorsal view; S, aedeagus, lateral view." pageId="1" pageNumber="376">Fig. 1R</figureCitation>
) with fine teeth along medial margin. Aedeagal shaft (
<figureCitation box="[160,278,1442,1468]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,248,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[263,1326,187,1892]" captionTargetId="figure-26@2.[259,1329,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. I. furcaprocessus sp. nov. A, F, K, holotype. A–E, adult, dorsal view; F–J, adult, lateral view; K–O, face; P, male pygofer and subgential plate, lateral view; Q, valve; R, connective, style and aedeagus, dorsal view; S, aedeagus, lateral view." pageId="1" pageNumber="376">Fig. 1R, S</figureCitation>
) wide and compressed, base expanded, with a pair of long preapical processes, each with short inner secondary process arising from near base.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1117,1936]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,453,1513,1540]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">Measurements (mm).</emphasis>
Male: body length 4.20–4.50, face length 1.10–1.30, width 1.20–1.40; distance between ocelli 0.40–0.50; distance from ocellus to eyes 0.20–0.30; medial length of pronotum 0.45–0.50, width 0.60–0.65; scutellum length 0.70–0.75, width 0.50–0.55.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
